I am not the type to drop reviews , however I couldn’t wait to share our recent experience at this restaurant in the heart of downtown Silverspring. Straight to the point I will say the service was outstanding , the servers were attentive although a little busy they did cater to our every need to effortlessly with this smile 😊.... And now onto the fooood! I really don’t know where to start! We had Guragee Kitfu which is similar to a Steak or lamb tartare mildly cookedor slightly raw with lots of home made Kebbee!!.. It was the closest to heaven one could think of literally... The juices were just so succulent, the butter was oh my! The cottage cheese paired well with the kotchoo. And to close it all the veggie combination was a rainbow of sensations on our pallets.. To be forewarned the potions are pretty huge .... The Ethiopian honey wine was semi sweet and paired well with the kitfu... That said Lucy Ethiopian restaurants is amongst the list of a thousand restaurants to visit b4 u kick the bucket 🌺

First review for me on google and it has to be for this poor excuse of a restaurant. August 7th at 8pm My family and I entered the establishment. We ordered some soft drinks and 4 different dishes, including rice for my little niece. There were around 5 tables with other customers and at least 3 of them were already eating at that time. We waited for more than an hour and each time we asked if the food is coming, we were told “it will arrive shortly.” Meanwhile even the people who came after us were getting their meals. The table next to us ordered a similar Rice dish as we did (for my niece) and they got it in less than 40 minutes. By this time, as anyone would expect, we were all furious with the service and asked for the manager. The waitress we spoke with went to the back to get the manger and stayed there for about 15 minutes. At which point one of us had to go back and ask what was going on. Another waitress informed us that there was no manger in the restaurant for the night. Our dinner was finally served at 9:10pm and another waitress approached us to apologize. When I asked her how come the table next to us got the rice order even though they got to the restaurant later than us, she replied that if she had known that was one of our order, it would have been served earlier. Our main waitress didn’t like the fact that we asked to see a manager and she couldn’t have been more rude for the rest of the night. For example, we asked for some napkins for the kids at least 6 times and it never arrived. Needless to say, I will not be eating at Lucy’s ever again.
